{"title_page": "Kartik Purnima (TV Show)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Kartik Purnima\n| image                    = \n| genre                    = [[Drama]] ,[[Romance]]\n| channel                  = [[Star Bharat]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[Hindi]], [[Punjabi]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 45 (as of 27 March 2020)\n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = \n| distributor              = [[Star India]]\n| picture_format           = \n| first_aired              = {{start date|df=yes|2020|2|03}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website            = https://www.hotstar.com/in/tv/kartik-purnima/s-2481\n| production_website = \n}}\n\n'''''Kartik Purnima''''' is an Indian Hindi-language social drama television series, which premiered on 3rd February 2020 on [[Star Bharat]]. It stars [[Poulomi Das]] who plays the role of a girl who has a dusky complexion who has to fight the social norm of not being fair skinned in India.\n\n==Plot==\nPurnima was treated unfairly from a young age because of her dark complexion. One day, young Purnima gives her trophy for student of the year to her step-sister, Shanaya, but is later caught as someone comes from her school revealing the truth. Purnima's father always stands for Purnima and asks Shanaya to apologise but she refuses. Later, her step-mother, who prefers her own daughter, abandons young Purnima at the Golden Temple. In search of her mother, young Purnima meets young Kartik who gives her a bracelet saying the bracelet will give her protection. Kartik's mother gets angry as her son is talking to a girl of dark complexion and middle-class. Purnima, nonetheless, reaches home and takes the blame of being a butterfly. Her father talks to her about how the way you act matters more than the colour of someone's skin complexion. \n\n16 years later, Purnima and Kartik are now adults. Kartik is a doctor who loves volunteering at the temple's footwear storage. While taking Purnima's footwear, he notices the bracelet. Kartik's mother, Soni, hates dark complexion as she is the owner of a fairness beauty brand and wishes for a fairy-like girl, fair complexion is a must. Purnima prays for her sister who is taking part at Miss Amritsar beauty. Purnima calls Shanaya and gives her a definition of beauty that was given to her by her father. Kartik overhears Purnima while he is consulting a patient and gets impressed by her thoughtfulness. Like the Arora sisters, the brothers have different definitions of beauty. When questioned by Soni, judge at the show, Shanaya gives the exacts same words Purnima told her. Kartik realises the similarity and concludes that Purnima might be nearby. Soni chooses Shanaya as her future daughter-in-law. Some time later, Kartik spots Purnima who was with her other family members. Soni sees her son and asks him what he was looking at. He points where and Soni sees Shanaya.\n\nNext morning, Soni and Sumreet (Kartik's brother) express their choices that matches, both being Shanaya. A boy comes for marriage proposal for Purnima but they reject her for her complexion. Shanaya is in need of money for another contest, Miss Punjab.\n\n\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Poulomi Das]] as Purnima Arora\n* Harsh Nagar as Kartik\n* Kavita Ghai as Soni, Kartik's mother\n\n===Recurring===\n'''''Surrounding Purnima'''''\n* Purnima's father\n* Purnima's grandmother\n* Purnima's step-mother\n* Nidhi Shah as Shanaya Arora, Purnima's step-sister\n\n\n'''''Surrounding Kartik'''''\n* Bijay Anand as Kartik's father\n* Mohit Chauhan as Kartik's father\n* [[Shraddha Jaiswal]] as Bably, Kartik's aunt\n* Twinkle, Kartik's cousin\n* Sumreet as Kartik's cousin\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian mythological television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Star Bharat television series]]\n\n== External links ==\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Kartik Purnima\n| image                    = \n| genre                    = [[Drama]] ,[[Romance]]\n| channel                  = [[Star Bharat]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[Hindi]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 45 (as of 27 March 2020)\n| producer                 = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = \n| distributor              = [[Star India]]\n| picture_format           = \n| first_aired              = {{start date|df=yes|2020|2|03}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website            = https://www.hotstar.com/in/tv/kartik-purnima/s-2481\n| production_website = \n}}\n\n'''''Kartik Purnima''''' is an Indian Hindi-language social drama television series, which premiered on 3rd February 2020 on [[Star Bharat]]. It stars [[Poulomi Das]] who plays the role of a girl who has a dusky complexion who has to fight the social norm of not being fair skinned in India.\n\n==Plot==\nPurnima was treated unfairly from a young age because of her dark complexion. One day, young Purnima gives her trophy for student of the year to her step-sister, Shanaya, but is later caught as someone comes from her school revealing the truth. Purnima's father always stands for Purnima and asks Shanaya to apologise but she refuses. Later, her step-mother, who prefers her own daughter, abandons young Purnima at the Golden Temple. In search of her mother, young Purnima meets young Kartik who gives her a bracelet saying the bracelet will give her protection. Kartik's mother gets angry as her son is talking to a girl of dark complexion and middle-class. Purnima, nonetheless, reaches home and takes the blame of being a butterfly. Her father talks to her about how the way you act matters more than the colour of someone's skin complexion. \n\n16 years later, Purnima and Kartik are now adults. Kartik is a doctor who loves volunteering at the temple's footwear storage. While taking Purnima's footwear, he notices the bracelet. Kartik's mother, Soni, hates dark complexion as she is the owner of a fairness beauty brand and wishes for a fairy-like girl, fair complexion is a must. Purnima prays for her sister who is taking part at Miss Amritsar beauty. Purnima calls Shanaya and gives her a definition of beauty that was given to her by her father. Kartik overhears Purnima while he is consulting a patient and gets impressed by her thoughtfulness. Like the Arora sisters, the brothers have different definitions of beauty. When questioned by Soni, judge at the show, Shanaya gives the exacts same words Purnima told her. Kartik realises the similarity and concludes that Purnima might be nearby. Soni chooses Shanaya as her future daughter-in-law.\n\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Poulomi Das]] as Purnima Arora\n* Harsh Nagar as Kartik\n* Kavita Ghai as Soni, Kartik's mother\n\n===Recurring===\n'''''Surrounding Purnima'''''\n* Nidhi Shah as Shanaya Arora, Purnima's step-sister\n\n'''''Surrounding Kartik'''''\n* Bijay Anand as Kartik's father\n* Mohit Chauhan as Kartik's father\n* [[Shraddha Jaiswal]] as Bably, Kartik's aunt\n* Twinkle, Kartik's cousin\n* Sumreet as Kartik's cousin\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian mythological television series]]\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Star Bharat television series]]\n\n== External links ==\n", "name_user": "Shameera1234", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kartik_Purnima_(TV_Show)"}
{"title_page": "B\u0103l\u0103ceana", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Suceava\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Suceava County\n|name=B\u0103l\u0103ceana\n|image_map              = Balaceana jud Suceava.png\n|image_shield=ROU SV Balaceana CoA.png\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|38|35|N|26|2|18|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''B\u0103l\u0103ceana''' is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] located in [[Suceava County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of a single village, B\u0103l\u0103ceana. This was part of [[Ili\u0219e\u0219ti]] Commune (theretofore called ''Ciprian Porumbescu'') until 2004, when it was split off, along with [[Ciprian Porumbescu, Suceava|Ciprian Porumbescu]] village; both formed separate communes.\n\n{{commons category|B\u0103l\u0103ceana commune, Suceava}}\n{{Suceava County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balaceana}}\n[[Category:Communes in Suceava County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Southern Bukovina]]\n{{Suceava-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Suceava\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Suceava County\n|name=B\u0103l\u0103ceana\n|image_map=\n|image_shield=ROU SV Balaceana CoA.png\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|38|35|N|26|2|18|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''B\u0103l\u0103ceana''' is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] located in [[Suceava County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of a single village, B\u0103l\u0103ceana. This was part of [[Ili\u0219e\u0219ti]] Commune (theretofore called ''Ciprian Porumbescu'') until 2004, when it was split off, along with [[Ciprian Porumbescu, Suceava|Ciprian Porumbescu]] village; both formed separate communes.\n\n{{commons category|B\u0103l\u0103ceana commune, Suceava}}\n{{Suceava County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balaceana}}\n[[Category:Communes in Suceava County]]\n[[Category:Localities in Southern Bukovina]]\n{{Suceava-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B%C4%83l%C4%83ceana"}
{"title_page": "2018 Swedish general election", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2018 Swedish general election\n| country = Sweden\n| type = parliamentary\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 2014 Swedish general election\n| previous_year = 2014\n| next_election = 2022 Swedish general election\n| next_year = ''Next''\n| seats_for_election = All 349 seats in the [[Riksdag]] <br /> 175 seats are needed for a majority\n| opinion_polls = Opinion polling for the Swedish general election, 2018\n| turnout = 6,532,063 (87.1%)<br />{{increase}} 1.3[[percentage point|pp]]\n| election_date = 9 September 2018\n| image1 = [[File:(Stefan L\u00f6fven) Viaje del presidente del Gobierno a Suecia.jpg|170x170px]]\n| colour1 = \n| leader1 = [[Stefan L\u00f6fven]]\n| leader_since1 = 27 January 2012\n| party1 = Swedish Social Democratic Party\n| alliance1 = [[L\u00f6fven I Cabinet|L\u00f6fven Cabinet]]<br />([[Red-Greens (Sweden)|Red-Greens]])\n| last_election1 = 113 seats, 31.0%\n| seats_before1 = 113\n| seats1 = 100\n| leaders_seat1 = [[V\u00e4sternorrland County]]\n| seat_change1 = {{decrease}} 13\n| popular_vote1 = 1,830,386\n| percentage1 = 28.3%\n| swing1 = {{decrease}} 2.7[[percentage point|pp]]\n| image2 = [[File:EPP Summit, 22 March 2018 (40954072911) (cropped).jpg|170x170px]]\n| colour2 = \n| leader2 = [[Ulf Kristersson]]\n| leader_since2 = 1 October 2017\n| party2 = Moderate Party\n| alliance2 = The Alliance (Sweden)\n| last_election2 = 84 seats, 23.3%\n| seats_before2 = 84\n| seats2 = 70\n| leaders_seat2 = [[S\u00f6dermanland County]]\n| seat_change2 = {{decrease}} 14\n| popular_vote2 = 1,284,698\n| percentage2 = 19.8%\n| swing2 = {{decrease}} 3.5[[percentage point|pp]]\n| image3 = [[File:Almedalen 7 July 2016 68 (27907007150) (cropped).jpg|170x170px]]\n| leader3 = [[Jimmie \u00c5kesson]]\n| leader_since3 = 7 May 2005\n| party3 = Sweden Democrats\n| alliance3 = \u2013\n| last_election3 = 49 seats, 12.9%\n| seats_before